4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING ELECTION LAWS; REVISING
5 ELECTIONS PROCEDURES ON INDIAN RESERVATIONS; REQUIRING AT LEAST ONE PERMANENT
6 SATELLITE OFFICE SELECTED BY EACH FEDERALLY RECOGNIZED INDIAN TRIBE IN CONSULTATION
7 WITH COUNTY OFFICIALS; REQUIRING PRECINCT POLLING PLACE NOTICES TO INCLUDE
8 LOCATIONS IN INDIAN RESERVATIONS; AUTHORIZING THE USE OF A NONTRADITIONAL ADDRESS AS
9 AN ELECTOR'S RESIDENTIAL ADDRESS FOR THE PURPOSES OF VOTER REGISTRATION AND
10 VOTING; AMENDING SECTIONS 13-2-110, 13-3-105, 13-13-114, 13-13-201, 13-15-107, AND 13-19-307,
11 MCA; AND PROVIDING A DELAYED EFFECTIVE DATE.”
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Permanent reservation satellite election offices. (1) For the purposes
16 of state and federal elections, a county shall establish at least one satellite election office within the boundaries
17 of an Indian reservation located within that county, unless the tribe, in consultation with the county, determines
18 that a satellite office is unnecessary. The tribal government of a federally recognized Indian tribe may select at
19 least one satellite election office location within the boundaries of the Indian reservation, or if the tribe does not
20 have a reservation, in a location that would best serve the members of the tribe.
21 (2) The satellite election office required in subsection (1) must be open no later than within 7 days
22 of the start of regular voter registration. The tribal government may set the days and hours of operation during
23 the period in which the satellite election office is operating in consultation with the county election administrator.
24 (3) A satellite office operated in accordance with subsection (1) shall provide services equivalent to
25 the services provided at the main election office of the county, including but not limited to:
26 (a) access to replacement ballots;
27 (b) in-person absentee voting; and
28 (c) late voter registration.
